  "suggestion": "[immunology+memory-systems+clinical-psychology+computational-neuroscience] IMPLEMENT NOW — Psychological Immune Memory (pattern repertoire). Add a `RESPONSE_LIBRARY: Array<{trigger: Partial<Situation>, response: Partial<Response>, strength: number}>` that acts like immunological memory. When a new situation arrives, compute cosine similarity against stored triggers. If similarity > threshold, blend matching responses weighted by similarity × strength. This explains: PTSD (hyper-activated pattern match), habituation (strength decays with safe exposures), automatic coping (fast response on re-encounter), overgeneralization (cross-reactivity). Implement as a lookup pass BEFORE the active-inference engine — if a strong pattern match (>0.8) is found, it short-circuits deliberative processing. ~40 lines of deterministic TypeScript. Concretely: 20 archetypal trigger-response pairs drawn from DSM/ICD, covering all 8 benchmark domains. — Math: response = Σ(similarity_i × strength_i × response_i) / Σ(similarity_i × strength_i) where similarity = dot(trigger_i, situation) / (|trigger_i| |situation|); [behavioral-economics+hyperbolic-discounting+self-regulation-theory+decision-neuroscience] IMPLEMENT NOW — Temporal Discounting Layer on top of the free-energy engine. Current model is stateless (no time dimension). Add a `timeHorizon` field derived from stimulus.timeConstraint and person arousal. Weight needs by hyperbolic discount factor: w(t) = 1/(1 + k·t) where k = impulsivity proxy (1 - conscientiousness). High arousal → k increases → extreme present-bias → safety/pleasure dominate. Low arousal + high conscientiousness → flat discount → achievement/autonomy dominate. This is a 1-line multiplicative modifier on the existing precision weights. Explains: stress-eating (high k, pleasure wins), procrastination (high k, pleasure > achievement), emergency heroism (safety for others discounted, esteem immediate), addiction cycles. — Math: precision_effective(need, t) = precision_base(need) × 1/(1 + k·t)  where k = 0.1 + 0.9×(1 - conscientiousness) × arousal, t = estimated horizon in normalized units; [topology+convex-geometry+self-concept-theory+social-psychology+cognitive-dissonance] Topological Identity Coherence — model each person as a simplex (convex hull) in trait-space. The 'self' is a region, not a point. Threats that push the predicted behavior OUTSIDE the self-simplex trigger identity-defense responses (reactance, cognitive dissonance, self-affirmation). Distance from simplex boundary determines response intensity. If predicted behavior lands inside the simplex: smooth adaptation. If outside: identity-protective resistance scales with boundary distance. This unifies: cognitive dissonance (behavior outside belief-simplex), reactance (autonomy boundary violation), conformity vs. rebellion (social pressure vector relative to identity simplex), and authenticity (how close to simplex centroid the behavior lands). Foundation: convex geometry + self-concept theory (Markus 1977) + reactance theory (Brehm 1966). — Math: identity_stress = max(0, d(predicted_behavior, self_simplex)) where d = distance from convex hull; response modulation = 1 + identity_stress × reactance_sensitivity",
